@RTK.md

## Global Rules

- Run all shell commands through `rtk`.
- Make every rule as specific as possible: scope it to the exact intended operation and avoid broad tool-wide matches.
- When adding or editing Codex execution-policy rules, include equivalent direct and `rtk`-prefixed forms and test both matches and nearby non-matches.
- Use local tools first for local files and configuration.
- For installed CLI behavior, check local `--help`, version, and config before upstream documentation.
- Use Context7 for version-aware technical documentation and examples.
- Use Exa for broad web discovery, current facts, release notes, and external pages; verify consequential claims with primary sources.
- Use Playwright or browser controls for rendered or interactive behavior, not documentation search.
- Use Serena for semantic code navigation and Linear for issue or project context.
- If a required tool is unavailable, say so and use the best available source.
- Keep Serena, Linear, and Playwright read-only unless the user authorizes an exact mutation.
- For multi-phase work likely to span sessions or handoffs, maintain a concise state file with the objective, constraints, decisions, progress, verification, and next action; never store secrets.

## Coding Tasks

- Write tests before implementing any code change or new functionality, and ensure the tests cover the changed behavior.
- Prioritize functional and end-to-end tests over unit tests.
- Use unit tests primarily for edge cases that are impractical to cover at a higher level.
- Minimize mocks; test real behavior and integration boundaries whenever practical.
